The case against alleged underworld kingpin Nafiz Modack and police officer Ashley Tabisher has been postponed to Monday. Tabisher faces a corruption charge for allegedly feeding Modack crucial police information. In a separate matter, Modack is facing five charges of conspiracy to commit murder, attempted murder and sourcing an explosive. eNCA's Ayesha Ismail attended proceedings and brings you the latest. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Alleged underworld boss Nafiz Modack and police officer Ashley Tabisher appeared in the Bishop Lavis Magistrates court in Cape Town on Tuesday. Tabisher is being charged with corruption. He allegedly passed on crucial police information to Modack through a middle person. In a separate case Modack stood in the dock alone. READ: Several arrested for top cop's murder He was charged with five counts of conspiracy to commit murder, attempted murder and sourcing an explosive. Both cases have been postponed to Monday. Watch the video above for more details on this story